                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/388: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-27T15:00:00-03:00"
                            >September 27, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 27—1:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>115. Disapprove Consul General <persName corresp="#p_CCR1">Cameron</persName>’s
                    recommendation in his telegram of September 27, noon, regarding a United States
                    warship which was made without consulting Embassy. His Majesty’s sloop <hi
                        rend="italic">Scars-borough</hi> arrived Rio de Janeiro today for an
                    ordinary official visit. This probably created report in São Paulo of British
                    measures for protection. Am familiar with Department’s telegraphic instruction
                    No. 60 of October 11, 2 p.m., 1930.<note n="5" xml:id="d455fn5">
                        <ref target="frus1930v01#pg_435">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1930, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 435</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MEV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
